timeline.bodyText:
Unnecessary coupling to Server, QuerySubscriber and ConnectionQueries?
Seems that this class could be decoupled from these types by having the QueryStreamHandler perform these two steps after constructing the ApiQuery:
 connectionQueries.addQuery(this);
    server.registerQuery(this);
And having ApiQuery constructor take a callback that will be called on close.  QueryStreamHandler can then pass in a lambda that does :
connectionQueries.removeQuery(this);
server.removeQuery(id);
 querySubscriber.close();
Which would result in less coupling (and more easily unit tested code)

